The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Record by Manavjit
                                                                                                                       7                                        Record by Manavjit
                  Manavjit                     
	New Delhi: Manavjit Singh Sandhu bettered the Commonwealth Games record in the individual trap event as Indian shooters won all the three gold medals on offer on the seventh day of the Commonwealth Championships, here on Wednesday.         
	Indias overall tally stood at 17 gold, 12 silver and six bronze medals. By adding the consolation badges given to the third shooter in a team event, Indias tally swells to 26 gold, 17 silver and 10 bronze.         
	Manavjit set a Commonwealth Games record in the mens trap individual event scoring 146 points to pocket the gold.         
	The other two golds for India came in the 10m air rifle womens event and 25m centre fire pistol competition for men. Neha Sapte won the gold in the womens 10m Air Rifle event scoring 496.1 points.         
	Indians swept all three medals in the mens 25m Centre Fire Pistol individual event. Vijay Kumar took the top spot with 580 points. Mahender Singh got the silver with 568 points, while Viraj Singh took the bronze for his 567 points.           (PTI)                                                                                                                 
